It should be noted that all the NO votes were "no, not ready for this particular draft, we need to agree on a resolution mechanism before we can include public identifiers." 
There is general agreement that XML will have public identifiers, but there has to be general agreement on a resolution mechanism before it shows up in the spec. 
XML 1.0 has a long way to go before it achieves "recommended" status. 
This feature just isn't cooked yet. 
Here is a quick rewrite of the XML catalog proposal with the extras removed. 
I don't know if this helps cook it or just adds too many chefs, but it provides something concrete and as simple as seems possible. 
