The SystemLiteral that may follow the entity's public identifier and the SystemLiteral that may follow the SYSTEM keyword are called the entity's system identifier. 
When an XML processor encounters an external entity defined by a public identifier, the processor determines the associated system identifier from a supplemental XML catalog (see 4.3.1). 
If the XML processor cannot successfully use or resolve the public identifer, and a system identifier follows the public identifier, the XML processor shall behave as if the system identifier was the only identifier supplied. 
